(Non-Empirical) In this analysis, Author D. Bar-Tal (1990) examines how misinformation among both groups, Israelis and Palestinians leads to cognitive discrepancy (Bar-Tal & Geva, 1985). Thus, finding a solution to this conflict is much more difficult when both sides have their own accountance of how conflict starts, how it was propagated, and how it continues to this day. This raises the question, is constructive discourse even possible between both sides?

Transition: After considering how misinformation festers from D. Bar-Tal (1990), we can further investigate the question of constructive discourse with a look into Gilovich & Ross's (2016) book on additional barriers that need to be overcame when it comes to negotations between differing parties.

